ine should never be reached given the problem constraints\n```\n\nThis solution works as follows:\n1. We create two arrays, `max_left` and `min_right`.\n2. `max_left[i]` will store the maximum value from the start of the array up to index `i`.\n3. `min_right[i]` will store the minimum value from index `i` to the end of the array.\n4. We iterate through the array to fill `max_left` and `min_right`.\n5. We then find the smallest index `i` such that `max_left[i - 1] <= min_right[i]`, which indicates the partition point.\n6. The length of the left subarray is `i`.\n\nThis approach ensures that we find the smallest possible left subarray that satisfies the conditions.", "estimated_date": 1538265600000}